39;,serif&quot;=\r\n&gt;Aatma does not have any name. Name accompanies form. As Aatma is\nbeyond an=\r\ny form, space or time, it does not have any name. Gnyaanis call it ParaBrah=\r\nma,\nYogis call it Aatma, Muslims call it Allah, Christian call it Father in=\r\n Heaven.\nThese names are given by us. Aatma on its own is nameless. Yet it =\r\nis our\nproblem that we need to call it or mention it with some name for our=\r\n\ndiscussion.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet [&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:philstinnet@ya=\r\nhoo.com&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;philstinnet@...&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;=\r\nspan style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,seri=\r\nf&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;P=\r\nalatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/2014 2:23 AM:]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span st=\r\nyle=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;div=\r\n class=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n2) Aatma just exists and nothing else exists.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Kannan:]&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Yes. Very Good. Whatever we see in this world is =\r\nAatma in form and\nname. But it is still Aatma. Like for example, we see a g=\r\nolden bangle. What\nexist? Gold? Or bangle? If I melt the bangle, it becomes=\r\n a lump of gold. So\ntechnically a bangle is a gold with a format. So this w=\r\norld we see is Aatma in a\nformat. What exists without format is Aatma, What=\r\n exists with format is Aatma\nagain. This is the true tatva-gnyaana that Gny=\r\naanis see. Avidya causes to see\nbangle in gold. And cry for bangle, when it=\r\n loses its format and becomes a lump\nof gold. They become happy when bangle=\r\n is formed out of gold and sad when\nbangle is dismantled back to gold. But =\r\nthere never existed any bangle before.\nSo how it can exist now? It is the g=\r\nold which is existing throughout.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nThus the &ldquo;existence&rdquo;=\r\n of this world is only in mind or imagination,\nnot in absolute sense. In ab=\r\nsolute sense, nothing exists other than Aatma.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet=\r\n [&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:philstinnet@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;philstinnet@ya=\r\nhoo.com&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-famil=\r\ny:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;f=\r\nont-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/201=\r\n4 2:23 AM:]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;=\r\nPalatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n3) Aatma has a center of=\r\n desire. The ability to have the desire is a permanent\nnature of Aatma.&lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Kannan:]&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Yes. Very Good. Aatma has Chitta where i=\r\nnfinite latent vrittis are in a\nseed form. To manifest itself from one to m=\r\nany during Srushti or Creation, and\nto squeeze itself from many to one, dur=\r\ning pralaya or dissolution, is like\nbreathing for Aatma. It cannot avoid th=\r\nis. It is its permanent nature. It is\nits defining characteristics. There i=\r\ns no reason for this, As it is beyond any\ncause-effect rule. This feature i=\r\ns like an Axiom which cannot be proven with a\nprecedence, because in order =\r\nto prove, we need a statement which is already\nproved. And to prove that on=\r\ne, we need another precedence statement, so\nultimately we need to start any=\r\n proof with an Axiom which on its own is\nproofless or does not require a pr=\r\noof. This is how Maths and Science are\nstudied. Every subject has an Axiom.=\r\n We cannot go on endlessly proving every\nstatement.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nFor example, i=\r\nn geometry, the first axiom defined by Euclid is &ldquo; A point\nis somethi=\r\nng which cannot be measured and has no dimension.&rdquo; Now, you\ncannot ex=\r\npect Euclid to prove this. Because these are Axioms. I hope it is\nclear.&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet [&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:philstinnet@...&quot; target=\r\n=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;philstinnet@...&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;f=\r\nont-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;=\r\n&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotyp=\r\ne&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/2014 2:23 AM:]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-siz=\r\ne:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n4) When Aatma has manifested itself in its &#39;desire&#39; form. It rema=\r\nins in the\nthree states - Waking, Dreaming, Sleeping.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\nYes. Very G=\r\nood.It witnesses all these states.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet [&lt;a href=3D=\r\n&quot;mailto:philstinnet@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;philstinnet@...&lt;/a&gt;]=\r\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palat=\r\nino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.=\r\n5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/2014 2:23 AM:]&lt;=\r\n/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Lin=\r\notype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n5) When Aatma is not in the &#39;des=\r\nire&#39; form. It is in the state of Moksha.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Kannan:]&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Yes. Very Good. Moksha is basically realizing one&rsquo;s true natu=\r\nre. Once\nAatma realizes its true nature, and gets freedom from Avidya or ig=\r\nnorance, it\nis Moksha indeed. In that case, Aatma dwells without forming an=\r\ny further vrittis\nout of avidya or ignorance, and burns it remaining vritti=\r\ns either though\nlifetimes or through the Grace of Guru Agni, which burns al=\r\nl vrittis. Without\nthe Grace-Agni of Guru, burning of vrittis is nearly imp=\r\nossible because there\nare infinite vrittis, and one has to take infinite li=\r\nfetimes to drain or\ndischarge them out, and in that process if one commits =\r\nor creates another\nvrittis, then the process is endless. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nShrimach=\r\n-Shankara-BhagavatPaada sang &ldquo;Punarapi Janamam, Punarapi Maranam,\nPun=\r\narapi Jananey Jatharey Shayanam,&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n&ldquo;Iha Sansaara, Bahu-Dustaara=\r\n, Krupaya Paarey, Paahi Muraarey&rdquo;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nMeaning, &ldquo;Again I ta=\r\nke birth, Again I die, Again I sleep in womb of my\nmother. This cycle of re=\r\npeated lifetime is very intriguing and complicated, Oh\nMuraari, please ferr=\r\ny me across this bottomless ocean of repeated lifetimes.&rdquo;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet [&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:philstinnet@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blan=\r\nk&quot;&gt;philstinnet@...&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:=\r\n10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u=\r\n&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,se=\r\nrif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/2014 2:23 AM:]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;=\r\nfont-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nIndeed it is a beautifu=\r\nlly written article. I have few questions &ndash;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Kannan:]=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Thanks again for your kind and well-meant appreciations. I wil=\r\nl be glad\nto answer provided with Grace and Blessings of The Ever-Existing =\r\nAatma in the\nform Shri Gurudeva.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet [&lt;a href=3D&quot;m=\r\nailto:philstinnet@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;philstinnet@...&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/=\r\nu&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatin=\r\no Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5p=\r\nt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/2014 2:23 AM:]&lt;/s=\r\npan&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linot=\r\nype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n1) Why does Aatma exist ?&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Kannan:]&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Let me do its mimaansa(analysis). Let me assume t=\r\nhat your question is\nvalid, and hence assume that there does exist a valid =\r\nanswer.&lt;br&gt;\nConsider Event A : &ldquo;aatma exist&rdquo;&lt;br&gt;\nConsider Event=\r\n B : &ldquo;reasons or cause for event A&rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;\nIf your answer is assu=\r\nmed to be existing, then event B must precede event A. In\nother words, even=\r\nt A cannot occur, unless and until event B has occurred.&lt;br&gt;\nNow, if your q=\r\nuestion is assumed to be a valid one, then event B must also\ncannot be stan=\r\nd-alone entity, but has to be supported by another preceding\nevent C.&lt;br&gt;\nA=\r\ngain, assuming your question to be valid and re-applied to event C, it must=\r\n\nhave another precedence event D..and so on..till infinite endless loop.&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\nIn mathematics, whenever we encounter, infinite loops or forms, we call i=\r\nt &ldquo;indeterminate&rdquo;\nor &ldquo;undefined&rdquo; like even in compu=\r\nter science you have this concept.\nIt&rsquo;s a hang-up.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSo it is =\r\nclear that answer to your question does not exist deterministically. In\nsuc=\r\nh case, the question becomes invalid.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNow why this invalidity is o=\r\nccurring for a simple question? Because, the\nquestion is valid only in doma=\r\nin of &ldquo;cause-effect&rdquo; linearity or\ncircularity. In such cases, y=\r\nou always have a preceding point for a given\npoint. Aatma is beyond all spa=\r\nce, time, cause, effect etc. So you cannot apply\nthis principle of &ldquo;c=\r\nause-effect&rdquo; to Aatma which itself is beyond\nthis frame of reference.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIn other words, you cannot discuss or understand Aatma logically =\r\nlike what we\ndo to other entities in day-to-day life.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nForget about=\r\n Aatma, take a very simple logical infinity loop, which fails\nmiserably to =\r\nattain a stable logical state. I give you that example as follows:&lt;br&gt;\n&nbs=\r\np;In logic or propositional calculus, a line is called &ldquo;statement&rdq=\r\nuo;,\nif it attains either a &ldquo;Truth value&rdquo;(Binary 1) or a &ldquo=\r\n;False\nvalue&rdquo;(Binary 0).But not both simultanesouly, of course.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\nCan you imagine a line which never attains any of the truth or false va=\r\nlue, but\nkeeps oscillating or shuttling between them? Well, let me share it=\r\n.&lt;br&gt;\nA person says :&rdquo; I always speak lies.&rdquo; Now, in logic, thi=\r\ns is not\ncalled a statement because it has no stable truth value or stable =\r\nfalse value. How?\nlet me explain.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIf the above line is true, then =\r\nwhatever he says is false(as he always speaks\nlies). If whatever he says is=\r\n false, then whatever he said must be\ntrue.(because he said that he always =\r\nspeak lies, and this is false, so he must\nbe speaking truth.)&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nPuzz=\r\nling? Well, this is called infinite loop or oscillation. The line &rdquo;I\n=\r\nalways speak lies&rdquo;, hence as per rules of propositional calculus, is =\r\nnot\na logical statement. So, logic fails miserably even in a mere line, the=\r\nn how it\ncan help us in defining or understanding Aatma?&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSo the bo=\r\nttomline is, Aatma is neither discussed nor explained nor logically\nverifie=\r\nd, rather it is realized. And one more thing, you cannot apply the\nconditio=\r\nn of &ldquo;cause-effect&rdquo; to one who is beyond all this. And your\nque=\r\nstion, is a typical &ldquo;cause-effect&rdquo; one; which violates head-on\n=\r\nthe very definition of Aatma as one beyond all cause-effect, space, time et=\r\nc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Phil Stinnet [&lt;a href=3D&quot;mailto:philstinnet@...&quot; t=\r\narget=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;philstinnet@...&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt; &lt;/span=\r\n&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Li=\r\nnotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;Sun\n3/16/2014 2:23 AM:]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;fon=\r\nt-size:10.5pt;font-family:&#39;Palatino Linotype&#39;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;=\r\n&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n2) Why does Aatma has this center of desire ? Who created it ?&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[Kannan:]&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt